RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 10800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 30 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEET FACTOR closed to the lead passing the thirteen sixteenths pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was pressured nearing the five sixteenths pole, drew off at the rail through the far turn and was kept alert to maintain her margin. SUPERSNAKE came away a bit awkwardly and rounded the first turn in the five path, started an outside bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn and cleared second in later yards. LADYNESS stalked from the four path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path, was carried out leaving the turn then dueled for third. RIDE THE RAPIDS stalked the early pace from the three path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path, drifted into the lane and relented in the stretch duel for third. ALL THE WAY MAE rounded the opening turn in the three path and showed little response through the backstretch. MAP THE MOMENT raced off the rail on the first turn and showed little response. WICKED SAUCY raced just off the early pace inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded past the three eighths.

ENTRY.NAME: Supersnake
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward break,5p 1st turn,bid 3/8,5p far turn,clear 2nd later yds

ENTRY.NAME: All the Way Mae
ENTRY.OWNER: Deiter Kelly Lynn and T J Albert Racing LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Factor
ENTRY.COMMENT: up past 13/16,rated pace inside,drew off,kept alert

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Claiming Purse 10800. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 30 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PATTI BLUE EYES set a pressured pace while tapering in through the backstretch, contested the edge two deep on the turn, dueled clear of It's A Real Honor passing the sixteenth pole and just lasted. JUJU ON DA BEAT gave chase through the backstretch, raced at the rail on the turn, dug in through the final furlong and just missed in a strong finish. IT'S A REAL HONOR pressured the pace inside, contested even terms at the rail on the turn but flattened the final sixteenth. POWER SONDE gave chase, raced in the four path on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. LET'S DO THIS chased, rounded the turn at the rail and flattened in the lane. WARRIORINTHEHOUSE saved ground. GOLDEN SALLY gave chase outside and raced wide on the turn. IMINCHARGENOW gave chase, rounded the turn in the three path and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Iminchargenow
ENTRY.OWNER: Ali Andrew and Schottroffe Edward T

ENTRY.NAME: Juju On Da Beat
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,rail turn,dug in lane,finished well,just missed

ENTRY.NAME: Patti Blue Eyes
ENTRY.OWNER: Fanelli John Cash is King LLC and LC Racing LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,edge 2d turn,clear past 1/16,just lasted

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 12300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eli gibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUD BUG took quick control of the pace inside, came under pressure past the three eighths pole and raced off the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady stretch encouragement and held on. TRANSFER THE FUNDS settled off the pace in the three path, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn, dug in while varying paths in the stretch and dueled for second. MASTER THIS settled off the pace in the five path, left the second turn outside and gave chase from the three eighths pole, had range on the leaders in the four path on the far turn but was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. URBAN BANDIT stalked the earlier pace from the three and four paths, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then weakened the final sixteenth. RIGHTEOUS MAN saved ground off the pace, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, drifted toward the head of the land and showed little further. ADARA raced well off the pace and off the rail early on, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the four and five paths and showed little in the lane. VOLIERO was not a factor. TIZBIT stalked the earlier pace off the rail, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but weakened past the three eighths. AKINGISALWAYSKING was not a factor. TYLER TIME stumbled at the break causing his rider to lose his irons but quickly recovered stride and rounded the first turn in the four path, gave way after a half mile and was eased the final quarter mile. The Stewards reviewed, then rejected a claim of foul against the rider of Mud Bug for alleged interference through the stretch, lodged by the rider of Transfer The Funds.

ENTRY.NAME: Mud Bug
ENTRY.OWNER: Prostar 10 Stables Inc and The Four Horsemen Racing Stable Inc
ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,rated pace,pressured 3/8,dug in lane,held on

ENTRY.NAME: Righteous Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 7/16,off rail far turn,drifted,empty lane

ENTRY.NAME: Adara
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace,off rail,chased 7/16,4& 5p far turn,empty lane

ENTRY.NAME: Transfer the Funds
ENTRY.OWNER: Gardner Sean and MIH Affiliates LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 13700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MARCH 30, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since March 30 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, al lowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOADED SNIPER exchanged contact with Big Hambone leaving the gate then pressured the pace, raced at a close disadvantage two deep on the turn but dug in determinedly through the stretch and took the nod in the final yards. STEVETHEVANDRIVER took over toward the half mile pole and moved to the inside to set a pressured pace, contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn, dug in gamely leaving the turn but grudgingly ceded the nod in the final yards. WIDGET FACTORY gave chase, rounded the turn in the three path, drifted leaving the turn then dueled through the stretch for third. BIG HAMBONE exchanged contact with Loaded Sniper leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch and rounded the turn in the five path, then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. DARK HEDGES chased, raced in the five path on the turn, lugged in through the lane and flattened stride. FLAMING EAST gave chase inside, rounded the turn near the rail and weakened in the lane. YABBA DABBA DUDE saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Dark Hedges
ENTRY.OWNER: Diamond Oak Stable and TEC Racing (Elliott S Logan)

ENTRY.NAME: Stevethevandriver
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,edge rail turn,gamely,ceded final yards

ENTRY.NAME: Loaded Sniper
ENTRY.OWNER: P and H Stables and C and B Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,pressed pace,close 2d turn,nod final yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 10800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: S S SPARTAN ENERGY raced in the five path the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole and steadily improved in the three and four paths on the far turn, dug in leaving the turn, took over and raced clear the final yards. WINDSOR'S TRACKER stalked two deep on the first turn, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, took the lead nearing the quarter and dug in under steady stretch handling, but was met and relented in later yards. RED DEVOLUTION was hustled with the early lead inside then rated into the first turn, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole, gave up the lead approaching the quarter, raced close at the rail on the far turn but flattened in the duel through the stretch. JONES FALLS saved early ground, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn and finished well. SPECTACULO stalked from the three path the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced close in the three path on the far turn but flattened the final sixteenth. ONLY GET'N BETTER raced well back inside, angled out leaving the far turn and could only improve his position. LUDO raced in the four path the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. SPEAK OF THE DEVIL settled off the rail, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. EISELE raced in the three and four paths the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. BRANTLEYS BIG GUN settled off the rail the first turn, gave chase past the half mile pole and entered the far turn about the six path, angled in through the turn and weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Brantleys Big Gun
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased past 1/2,6p into far turn,angled in,weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Starter Allowance Purse 18600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE SEPTEMBER 30, 2021. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 30 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 30 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races W here Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADVANCE CASH came in early then gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and was steadily handled to widen later yards. GOLDEN G gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn, dug in to take second later yards and finished well. MR TINGLES took over while angling inward and rated the early pace, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, was met mid-stretch and flattened later yards. INSIDE RISK gave chase outside, raced in the five path on the turn and ran evenly down the lane. HEY CONGRATS gave chase, raced in the five and six paths on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. COWBOY AT HEART was shut off and clipped the heels of STRETCH THE TRUTH early then picked up the chase, was eased to the four path approaching the head of the lane but showed little further. The latter was forced inward and into Cowboy At Heart early and had his heels clipped as a result, gave chase from that point but flattened at the rail on the turn. NITRO TIME was unprepared for the break then saved ground. The Stewards reviewed a claim of foul against the rider of Advance Cash for interference soon after the start, lodged by the rider of Cowboy At Heart, and disqualified the former to sixth place for causing the interference that affected the latter.

ENTRY.NAME: Cowboy At Heart
ENTRY.COMMENT: shut off early,clipped heels,chased inside,4p 1/8,little left

ENTRY.NAME: Golden G
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,up 2nd later yards,finished well

ENTRY.NAME: Stretch the Truth
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in,heels clipped early,chased,flattened rail turn

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Advance Cash
ENTRY.COMMENT: came in early,chased,3p turn,up 1/16,widened later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 28400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 30 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 30 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races W here Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NO DENYING DENIS ducked in leaving the gate and made contact with Lucky Bop then settled off the rail on the first turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, steadily improved from that point and rounded the far turn about the five path, dug in leaving the turn and took the lead in the final strides. JUBASLILBALLERINA rounded the first turn about the five path then stalked three wide into the backstretch, challenged approaching the three eighths pole, dueled for the lead midway on the far turn and dug in determinedly to eke out the advantage over MARINA GRANDE but was caught in the final strides. The latter was forced in and into Slewing leaving the gate then took the nod two deep at the nine sixteenths pole, was met approaching the three eighths and dueled at a close disadvantage from that point and dug in gamely to the finish. SILVER RULES rated close inside on the opening turn then picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path but flattened stride mid-stretch. SLEWING was brushed leaving the gate then settled off the rail, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and flattened in the lane. LUCKY BOP came away awkwardly and was bumped then forced inward and into Marina Grande, rounded the first turn about the four path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and showed little further. JACKYSINTHECASTLE saved ground. LOVE OF GRACE raced with the pace inside and dueled from the three eighths pole, was met toward the quarter and weakened at the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Love of Grace
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace inside,dueled from 3/8,met 1/4,weakened rail turn

ENTRY.NAME: Marina Grande
ENTRY.OWNER: Jay A Reese LLC and Hatter Edgar

ENTRY.NAME: No Denying Denis
ENTRY.COMMENT: ducked in,bumped,off rail,bid 7/16,5p far turn,up final strides

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Purse 27400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners O f A Race Since August 30 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 30 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUBA'S PARADE raced in the five path the first turn, rallied to the lead two deep approaching the quarter pole, drew clear midway on the far turn and was steadily handled to hold on well. SUMMERTIME ROSE rated a short lead inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, was met approaching the quarter, rounded the far turn near the rail and dug in to hold onto second. HESSICA rounded the opening turn in the three path, picked up the chase toward the five sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little further. JACK'S LILLY raced two deep on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded past the three eighths. BOUNDTOBEOK tapered in and stalked the early pace from the three path, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the four path on the far turn. SWEET TALIA saved ground. JUBA BABY raced inside, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole then weakened at the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Juba Baby
ENTRY.OWNER: Two Ten Twelve Triple T Racing

ENTRY.NAME: Juba's Parade
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5p 1st turn,rallied to lead 2d nearing 1/4,clear turn,held well

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 9 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 48. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASTRAYAL settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn about the four path, left the turn in the five path and dug in to take over the final strides while edging out DENIZETTI the length of the stretch. The latter rounded the first turn in the four and five paths, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the five path and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. COLONIAL ROAD raced in the six path the first turn then stalked into the backstretch, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, dueled for the nod three wide midway on the far turn but was caught flattening stride the final yards. LAST PARTY steadied off the heels of LORD CLANCY into the first turn then stalked off the rail, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, dueled at even terms between horses leaving the quarter and raced two deep through the far turn, but flattened stride later yards. The latter took the lead at the three quarter pole, angled to the inside into the first turn and rated the pace, came under pressure toward the three eighths pole, was met at the rail midway on the far turn and dug in under steady handling, but flattened stride later yards. LITTLE RICHIE saved ground on the first turn then picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and flattened the final sixteenth. IRISH FLIGHT raced in the four path the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the four path on the far turn. JUBA'S MOCHA checked off the heels of Little Richie into the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. RAISE A RUCKUS rated close inside on the opening turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened at the rail into the far turn. GETTIN SPICY saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Raise a Ruckus
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,chased 7/16,weakened rail into far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Last Party
ENTRY.OWNER: Don't Chasem Replacem Racing and Armstrong Katina M
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied into 1st turn,stalked off rail,chased 3/8,flattened late

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Clancy
ENTRY.COMMENT: up 3/4,rated pace inside,pressured 3/8,met mid turn,flatten late
